    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of the plan I've written:\n\n## Plan: `image-text-to-text` Pipeline\n\n**Only one file needs to change:** `src/pipelines.js`\n\nThe infrastructure is already fully in place — `AutoModelForImageTextToText`, model-specific processors (LLaVA, PaliGemma, Qwen2-VL, etc.), and the `generate()` machinery all exist in `src/models.js`. The pipeline layer is the only missing piece.\n\n### 5 insertions into `src/pipelines.js`:\n\n| # | Where | What |\n|---|---|---|\n| 1 | Import block (~line 44) | Add `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the named import from `./models.js` |\n| 2 | After line 1953 | Add 3-typedef JSDoc block (`ImageTextToTextSingle`, `…Output`, `…PipelineCallback`, `…PipelineType`) |\n| 3 | After line 2005 | Add the `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class (~30 lines) |\n| 4 | After line 3255 | Add `\"image-text-to-text\"` entry in `SUPPORTED_TASKS` |\n| 5 | ~line 3427 | Add one bullet to the `pipeline()` JSDoc task list |\n\n**Key implementation details for the class:**\n- Extends `Pipeline` using `TextImagePipelineConstructorArgs` (tokenizer + processor + model) — same as `ImageToTextPipeline`\n- `_call(images, text, generate_kwargs = {})` — the two required inputs\n- Images are prepared via the existing `prepareImages()` helper; a single text string is broadcast across all images in a batch\n- Each image+text pair is processed **one at a time** through `this.processor(image, text)` (which handles model-specific token fusion internally), then `this.model.generate()`, then decoded via `this.tokenizer.batch_decode()`\n- Return shape mirrors `ImageToTextPipeline`: `[{generated_text}]` for single, `[[{generated_text}], ...]` for batched\n\n**No existing classes are modified.**",
